<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Doer" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Doer,</orth> 1) one who has done any thing: Lucr. Arg. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 26</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.133" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 3, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.154" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 154</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 1, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 1, 15</bibl>.<lb />2) one who is wont and ready to act: <cit><quote>great --s in our trade,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 20</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>talkers are no good --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.352" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 352</bibl></cit>.
